The bony deflection was removed using Jansen-Middleton forceps.

A mucoperichondrial flap was carefully elevated, and the junction with the cartilaginous bony septum was separated with the Freer elevator. The bony deflection was removed using Jansen-Middleton forceps.
The initial incision was placed in its anatomical position and secured with a 4-0 nylon suture for stabilization effect.
